{{Refimprove|date=May 2016}} {{Infobox number | number = 243 }} '''243''' ('''two hundred [and] forty-three''') is the [[natural number]] following [[242 (number)|242]] and preceding [[244 (number)|244]].
==In mathematics== 243 is: *the only 3-digit number that is a fifth power (3<sup>5</sup>). *a [[perfect totient number]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oeis.org/A082897|title=Sloane's A082897 : Perfect totient numbers|last=|first=|date=|website=The On-Line Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences|publisher=OEIS Foundation|access-date=2016-05-28}}</ref> *the sum of five consecutive [[prime number]]s (41 + 43 + 47 + 53 + 59). *an 82-[[Polygonal number|gonal number]]. *a [[Harshad number]].
==In other fields== 243 is: * the Calling code for the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]], the country once known as [[Zaire]]. * the year [[243|243 AD]] or [[243 BC]]. * [[Aloha Airlines Flight 243]] which suffered an explosive decompression near [[Maui, HI]] on April 28, 1988 * [[.243 Winchester]] and [[.243 Winchester Super Short Magnum|.243 WSSM]], rifle rounds * The number of Earth Days for the planet Venus to complete one Venusian day, one revolution
