In [[quantum information theory]], the '''identity channel''' is a noise-free [[quantum channel]]. That is, the channel outputs exactly what was put in.<ref>{{citation|title=Quantum Information Theory|first=Mark|last=Wilde|publisher=Cambridge University Press|year=2013|isbn=9781107034259|page=618|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=T36v2Sp7DnIC&pg=PA618}}.</ref>

The identity channel is commonly denoted as <math>I</math>, <math>\mathsf{id}</math> or <math>\mathbb{I}</math>.

