{{eastern name order|Vesztergombi Katalin}} {{Infobox academic | honorific_prefix = <!-- see [[MOS:HONOURIFIC]] --> | name = Katalin Vesztergombi | honorific_suffix = | image = Katalin Vesztergombi.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | birth_name = <!-- use only if different from full/othernames --> | birth_date = 1948 <!-- {{birth date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) --> | death_place = | death_cause = | region = | nationality = Hungarian | citizenship = | residence = | other_names = | occupation = | period = | known_for = | title = | boards = <!--board or similar positions extraneous to main occupation--> | spouse = | children = | awards = <!--notable national level awards only--> | website = | education = Fazekas Mihály Gimnázium | alma_mater = Eötvös Loránd University | thesis_title = Distribution of Distances in Finite Point Sets | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | school_tradition = | doctoral_advisor = Vera Sós | academic_advisors = | influences = <!--must be referenced from a third party source--> | era = | discipline = Mathematics | sub_discipline = <!--academic discipline specialist area – e.g. Sub-atomic research, 20th Century Danish specialist, Pauline research, Arcadian and Ugaritic specialist--> | workplaces = Eötvös Loránd University | doctoral_students = <!--only those with WP articles--> | notable_students = <!--only those with WP articles--> | main_interests = | notable_works = ''Discrete Mathematics: Elementary and Beyond'' | notable_ideas = | influenced = <!--must be referenced from a third party source--> | signature = | signature_alt = | signature_size = | footnotes = }} '''Katalin L. Vesztergombi''' (born 1948){{r|hdc}} is a Hungarian mathematician known for her contributions to [[graph theory]] and [[discrete geometry]]. A student of [[Vera T. Sós]] and a co-author of [[Paul Erdős]], she is an emeritus associate professor at [[Eötvös Loránd University]]{{r|elte}} and a member of the [[Hungarian Academy of Sciences]].{{r|mta}}
==Education== As a high-school student in the 1960s, Vesztergombi became part of a special class for gifted mathematics students at [[Fazekas Mihály Gimnázium (Budapest)|Fazekas Mihály Gimnázium]] with her future collaborators [[László Lovász]], József Pelikán, and others.{{r|tgl}} She completed her Ph.D. in 1987 at Eötvös Loránd University.{{r|hdc|mgp}} Her dissertation, ''Distribution of Distances in Finite Point Sets'', is connected to the [[Erdős distinct distances problem]] and was supervised by Vera Sós.{{r|mgp}}
==Contributions== Vesztergombi's research contributions include works on [[permutation]]s,{{ran|PR}} [[graph coloring]] and [[graph product]]s,{{ran|XN}} combinatorial [[discrepancy theory]],{{ran|SS}} distance problems in [[discrete geometry]],{{ran|LD}} [[geometric graph theory]],{{ran|GR}} the [[Crossing number (graph theory)|rectilinear crossing number]] of the [[complete graph]],{{ran|CQ}} and [[graphon]]s.{{ran|D1}}{{ran|D2}}
With [[László Lovász]] and József Pelikán, she is the author of the textbook ''Discrete Mathematics: Elementary and Beyond''.{{r|dm}}{{ran|DM}}
==Personal== Vesztergombi is married to [[László Lovász]], with whom she is also a frequent research collaborator.{{r|nol}}
